{"id":14880795,"mediaExerciseId":"5db24ed5-aec7-4c48-b6f7-8e5dc20c8113","exerciseName":"12","chapterName":"3","chapterTitle":"Working with Financial Statements","groupId":612274,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":85,"solutions":[{"id":5933729,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to determine the effect on the statement of cash flows and how sustainable the change in cash flows is if a company lengthens the time it takes to pay suppliers.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define cash flow statements.\n\n**Cash flow statements** is a financial statement that analyzes the changes in cash and cash equivalents for a period.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/24/95d3c46d546bcbb5245ea16aae025a79/d89ae1184ee77cda1062505be61ac5a0/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/24/95d3c46d546bcbb5245ea16aae025a79/d89ae1184ee77cda1062505be61ac5a0/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"If the company decides to lengthen the time it takes to pay suppliers, this would increase the company's operating cash flows since the company holds on to cash for a longer period. This can affect the sustainability of the company and its relationship from suppliers. The company should build a good relationship with its suppliers for improved products, good deals, and favorable lines of credit.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/24/95d3c46d546bcbb5245ea16aae025a79/395a3a4b1fa9e4adcb7476fa1f78957d/lateximg_large.png","width":994},"r